<h3>End Game</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Trigger: any objective card condition is met OR rebellion marker moves past population marker</li>
    <li>Card objective: game ends at the end of active player's turn</li>
    <li>No points for triggering end game</li>
    <li>Separatist wins alone in event of rebellion, but can still score points and win when no rebellion occurs</li>
    <li>Pacifist scores 3 points alone if their condition is met</li>
    <li>Score for <i>every</i> objective card criteria, the trend card, and certain evolution cards</li>
    <li>0 points if no contribution to point condition</li>
    <li>Ties are friendly: 5-5-3-2-0 distributes points as 3-3-2-1-0</li>
    <li>Score trend card the same way</li>
    <li>Benefactor: add $1 from bank to corresponding color zone whenever that player contributes a cube for a crisis, or when building a temple</li>
    <li>Score evolution cards with points on them</li>
    <li>Tie breaker: money</li>
    <li>Uncontrolled buildings only contribute to end-game conditions, otherwise they must be controlled for any in-game effects</li>
</ul>

<h3>2-player</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Remove pacifist & separatist</li>
    <li>2 objectives per player</li>
    <li>Red/Yellow vs Green/Blue</li>
    <li>5 AD limit per player</li>
</ul>

