<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>1. Disengagement</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Skip in turn 1</li>
                <li>Reset cards owned by players</li>
                <li>Citizens and ships move off resources</li>
                <li>Rebel citizens stand up</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>2. Order of Play</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Secret bids, all money to bank</li>
                <li>Bid winner decides order for all players</li>
                <li>No bids <span class="arrow"></span> turn order is unchanged</li>
                <li>Tie: tied players bid again; another tie <span class="arrow"></span> turn order unchanged</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>3. Population Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Board I: for each resource, adjust worker and rebellion markers</li>
                <li>Board II: same as board I</li>
                <li>Board III: adjust worker & rebellion markers using pop. marker</li>
                <li>Board IV: adjust rebellion marker using worker marker</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Balance of the Archipelago</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Skip in turn 1</li>
                <li>Ignore red zones, resolve any revealed tan zone</li>
                <li>A crisis may be repeated multiple turns</li>
                <li>Domestic crisis
                    <ul>
                        <li>lay down all citizens</li>
                        <li>provide resources in turn order, once around the table</li>
                        <li>contribute from domestic market (free) or personal supply</li>
                        <li>stand up X citizens per cube, cannot stand up fewer</li>
                        <li>advance rebellion marker 1 per rebel</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Export crisis
                    <ul>
                        <li>provide resources in turn order, once around the table</li>
                        <li>contribute from export market (free) or personal supply</li>
                        <li>advance rebellion marker 1 per missing resource</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Events ignore whether the building is controlled</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>5. Actions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>3 discs, unlock another disc each time an exploration pile is emptied</li>
                <li>Limited actions: taxes, reproduction, exploration</li>
                <li>All other actions are unlimited</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>6. Evolution Card Purchase</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Clear action wheel</li>
                <li>In turn, either
                    <ul>
                        <li>purchase a card then rotate another, or</li>
                        <li>rotate 2 different cards</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Discard if pointing at skull</li>
                <li>After purchase / rotation, fill empty spaces one at a time</li>
                <li>Resolve red-zone crises immediately, similar to phase 4</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Adding a Hex</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Increase surplus workers by number of huts</li>
                <li>Choose 1 circle <span class="arrow"></span> add cube to domestic market</li>
                <li>Choose another resource circle <span class="arrow"></span> add cube to personal supply</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h4>Engaged</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>These actions engage a unit
                    <ul>
                        <li>harvest</li>
                        <li>construction of a <i>building</i></li>
                        <li>using a port or market</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Engaged units can reproduce and recruit</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Evolution cards</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>can only be used during action phase</li>
                <li>1 card per turn</li>
                <li>pay [cost+1] to the owner if activating another player's card</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Explorer Tokens</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>can only be converted for crisis resolution or during actions</li>
                <li>Empty stack immediately unlocks extra action disc</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Independence</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>the rebellion marker moves <i>past</i> the population marker</li>
                <li>game ends, all players lose except the separatist</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Hex Limits</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Max 3 citizens per color per region</li>
                <li>Limit does not block other colors</li>
                <li>No ship limits</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Meeples</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><u>Unit</u> ship or citizen (active or rebel)</li>
                <li><u>Active Unit</u> active citizen or ship</li>
                <li>Citizens can be active/rebel, engaged/non-engaged</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Rebel Citizens</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>cannot perform actions</li>
                <li>cannot use/control a building</li>
                <li>no money contribution during taxes</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Sea Inlets</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Citizens on opposite banks of a sea
                    <ul>
                        <li>cannot reproduce</li>
                        <li>cannot harvest on the other bank</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Ships can recruit to either bank</li>
                <li>Towns control both sides, temples affect both sides</li>
                <li>During turn 0 exploration, may deploy to either/both banks</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Wonders</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Must be built for the reward (construction icon)</li>
                <li>Takes the card activation for the turn, not the action</li>
                <li>Requires active non-engaged citizen</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

